properties.areaDesc: White Mountains of Inyo County; Death Valley National Park; Owens Valley; Eastern Sierra Slopes of Inyo County
properties.headline: High Wind Warning issued February 1 at 11:37PM PST until February 3 at 6:00PM PST by NWS Las Vegas NV
properties.description:
* WHAT...Southwest to west winds of 25 to 35 mph with gusts up to
50 mph will initially develop Sunday afternoon. By the evening
hours, winds will shift to the northwest increasing to 35 to 45
mph with gusts up to 70 mph possible.

* WHERE...Inyo County California including the Owens Valley and
Death Valley. This includes the California cities of Bishop,
Independence, Aspendell, Death Valley Junction, Furnace Creek,
Olancha, and Shoshone.

* WHEN...From 4 PM PST Sunday to 6 PM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Very dangerous driving conditions for travelers along
Highway 395, especially from Independence, to Olancha, and
south to Inyokern. High profile vehicles are especially
vulnerable to being blown over due to extreme west winds
impacting this north- south highway. Additionally, multiple and
possibly long duration power outages are expected for all of
Inyo County. Downed trees and power poles are possible county-
wide as well. Securing any loose items such as trash cans,
outdoor plants, sports equipment, or trampolines, is highly
recommended. Areas of blowing dust are also possible.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...These winds are expected to originally
increase out of the southwest, shift to the west, and then to
the northwest as a cold front pushes through. Winds will begin
to subside Monday morning but could remain elevated through the
afternoon hours.
properties.instruction:
People should avoid being outside in forested areas and around
trees and branches. If possible, remain in the lower levels of
your home during the windstorm, and avoid windows. Use extreme
caution if you must drive, especially if you are operating a
semi-truck or panel truck with a wide trailer.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 4 PM SUNDAY TO 6 PM PST MONDAY
